verbose_text: The migration of HUVECs with a reduced AJAP1 expression was faster, resulting in a remaining average wound size of 14.7% (siAJAP1-1), 10.3% (siAJAP1-2, P < 0.05), 6.5% (siAJAP1-3, P < 0.001) and 12.9% (pooled siRNA) compared to the control, which had a remaining wound area of 32.2% 8 h following wound setting (XREF_FIG A, B).
